$interpreted: Sharice: Rat monster!?

Yan-Bo: Been a while, it has. Energetic as always, I see.
If that's the case, exercise our bodies, shall we?
Yan-Bo: Not bad, not bad. Time for me to get serious, I presume.
Yan-Bo: Young lady, lost, you have.
Sharice: You damn rat monster...
Yan-Bo: Now, reason why you wanted mermaid scales, tell.
Sharice: Why are you asking?
Yan-Bo: To ask for forgiveness from Hestia for you, of course.
Sharice: .... Eh? But you're much stronger than me. You don't have to care about me...
Yan-Bo: Must be strongest for others to be willing to offer a helping hand, why this you so firmly believe?
Yan-Bo: Apologize sincerely to Hestia; the only thing you must do now, that is.
Sharice: ... But my father...
Sharice: Ever since my much brighter little brother was born, my father has only cared about him. That's why I enlisted in the army in the first place...
Yan-Bo: I see. So persistent about being the strongest, is that reason why?

Sharice: As long as I'm the strongest, the best I can be, I won't be abandoned... or so I thought. 
But in reality...
Yan-Bo: In reality, turn out as you expected, things did not. Am I right?

Sharice: I genuinely dislike my little brother.
Ever since he was born, my father stopped caring about me.
Sharice: However, despite all these things, I still can't just sit and watch him suffer like that...
Yan-Bo: So to cure brother's disease, reason you want the scales?
Yan-Bo: Heard about such a treatment method, indeed I have...

Yan-Bo: Young one, represent everyone else, your father does not. You are who you are.
People who truly care about you, strongest or not, will always continue to care about you, no matter what.
Yan-Bo: Don't you agree, Hestia?
Hestia: I just... I just don't like to be called fish freak.
Hestia: If it's something as important as saving a life, just ask me nicely. I am more than willing to help you out...
Yan-Bo: Understand what you should do now, don't you, young lady?

Sharice: ... What I did back there... I'm sorry.
I promise I will not call you fish freak again.
Sharice: ... I want to save my little brother. Could you please give me some of your scales?
Jerome: Hey! Is Sharice late again?
Sharice: R, report... I'm here...
Jerome: Carterwell, nobody told you the time for morning practice again?
Sharice: ... I...
Grouchy Soldier: She's not going to admit that she was bullied. For someone who can't shut up about being the GOAT, she'll never admit something this humiliating...
Sharice: No Sir. This time, it's because I couldn't find my uniform after I woke up. Only until later did I discover that someone hid it.
Jerome: ... Someone hid your uniform?

Jerome: Do you bastards have too much free time!?
Seems like you do cause you have time for stupid tricks like this!
Jerome: After the training is over, thirty laps for all of you!!

Grouchy Soldier: Didn't expect you to rat us out to the captain...
How dare you call yourself the GOAT.

Sharice: I am indeed not the greatest of all time.
However, I at least have the dignity to not resort to bullying others behind their back!
Sharice: Also, no matter what kind of crap you people throw at me, I will definitely arrive earlier than any of you next time!

Sharice: Because even though I'm not the greatest,
I am still who I am, and I am Sharice Carterwell~!! Hahahaha!

Grouchy Soldier: ... Damnit, I can't believe that she was kind of cool just now...
I must be hallucinating....
Cruel Soldier: ... Hey, we already got busted by the captain anyway. Let's stop with the petty tricks.
Grouchy Soldier: ... Yeah...
